            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–2246</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-22T13:00:00+08:00">October 22, 1946—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 22—10:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1711. Minority party leaders, top Government representatives and others, having
                    persuaded Chou En-lai to return to capital from Shanghai with them, President
                    Chiang sent for me on morning of October 21, before leaving for Formosa, to
                    define his policy as follows:</p>
                <p>Having formally delivered his published communication of October 18 [<hi rend="italic">16</hi>] through General Marshall and me to the Communist
                    delegates, he indicated they should in like manner send a written reply. If
                    favorable, the discussions should follow the procedure and be confined within
                    the terms of his communication. Every encouragement should be given the minority
                    parties to take an active share in preparation for and joining in the National
                    Assembly.</p>
                <p>Generalissimo’s trip to Formosa had been long planned and his departure postponed
                    one day in order to see Chou and minority party leaders, its coming at this time
                    being purely a coincidence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
